attrs.script:
Get-Disk -Number 1 | Initialize-Disk -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
New-Partition -DiskNumber 1 -UseMaximumSize -AssignDriveLetter -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Format-Volume -Confirm:$false

# Mssql 2014 (Express,Standard or datacenter)
	$DriveLetter = $(Get-Partition -DiskNumber 1 -PartitionNumber 2 | select DriveLetter -ExpandProperty DriveLetter)
    $TempDirectory = "C:\Temp"
    $HOSTNAME=$(hostname)
    $PackageName = "MsSqlServer2014Express"
        
    $silentArgs = "/IACCEPTSQLSERVERLICENSETERMS /Q /ACTION=install /INSTANCEID=SQLEXPRESS /INSTANCENAME=SQLEXPRESS /UPDATEENABLED=FALSE /INDICATEPROGRESS"
    $filePath = "$TempDirectory\SQLEXPR_x64_ENU.exe"
    $extractPath = "$TempDirectory\SQLEXPR_x64_ENU"
    $setupPath = "$extractPath\setup.exe"
    $fileType = 'exe'
    $validExitCodes = @(0, 3010)
   
    


    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path $TempDirectory
    $adminpassword = ConvertTo-SecureString -asPlainText -Force -String "Nutanix.123"
    $c = New-Object System.Management.Automation.PSCredential("administrator", $adminpassword)
    New-PSDrive -Name "P" -PSProvider "FileSystem" -Root "@@{EXE_SHARE_PATH}@@" -Credential $c
    
    Copy-Item -Path "P:\SQLEXPR_x64_ENU.exe" -Destination $TempDirectory
    
    if ($Prerequisites){
        Install-WindowsFeature -IncludeAllSubFeature -ErrorAction Stop $Prerequisites
    }

    if ($fileType -eq 'exe'){
        Write-Output "Extracting..."
        Start-Process "$filePath" "/Q /x:`"$extractPath`"" -Wait -NoNewWindow -PassThru
    } elseif ($fileType -eq 'iso'){
          $setupDriveLetter = (Mount-DiskImage -ImagePath $filePath -PassThru | Get-Volume).DriveLetter + ":"
          $setupPath = "$setupDriveLetter\setup.exe"
    }
    Write-Output "Installing $PackageName...."

    $install = Start-Process -FilePath $setupPath -ArgumentList $silentArgs -Wait -NoNewWindow -PassThru
    $install.WaitForExit()
    $exitCode = $install.ExitCode
    $install.Dispose()

    Write-Output "Command [`"$setupPath`" $silentArgs] exited with `'$exitCode`'."
    if ($validExitCodes -notcontains $exitCode) {
        Write-Output "Running [`"$setupPath`" $silentArgs] was not successful. Exit code was '$exitCode'. See log for possible error messages."
    }
